                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 K 55/129: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-23T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Advise Nansen of substance of Riga’s No. 444, June 21, which Riga is
                    repeating to you and inquire if Nansen has made any progress toward release of
                    Americans.</p>
                <p>Let him know that situation reported by Riga is regarded by this Government as
                    most serious and that consideration is being given to every possible means of
                    terminating it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
